03654 c      Given a set of data points x(1: ndata),y(1: ndata) 
03655 c      with individual standard deviations
03656 c      sig(1: ndata), fit them to a straight line y = a + bx 
03657 c      by minimizing x2. 
03658 c      Returned are a, b and their respective probable uncertainties siga and sigb, 
03659 c      the chi-square chi2, and or the goodness-of-fit probability q 
03660 c      (that the fit would have x2 this large or larger). If mwt=0
03661 c      on input, then the standard deviations are assumed to be unavailable: q 
03662 c      is returned as 1. and the normalization of chi2 is to unit standard deviation 
03663 c      on all points.
03664 
03665       SUBROUTINE fit(x,y,ndata,sig,mwt,a,b,siga,sigb,chi2,q)
03666       INTEGER mwt ,ndata
03667       REAL a,b,chi2,q,siga,sigb,sig(ndata),x(ndata),y(ndata)
03668       INTEGER i
03669       REAL sigdat,ss,st2,sx,sxoss,sy,t,wt,gammq
03670       sx=0.
03671       sy=0.
03672       st2=0. 
03673       b=0.
03674       if(mwt.ne.0) then 
03675         ss=0.
03676         do i=1,ndata
03677           wt=1./(sig(i)**2)
03678           ss=ss+wt
03679           sx=sx+x(i)*wt
03680           sy=sy+y(i)*wt
03681         enddo
03682       else
03683         do i=1,ndata
03684           sx=sx+x(i)
03685           sy=sy+y(i)
03686         enddo 
03687         ss=float(ndata)
03688       endif
03689       sxoss=sx/ss
03690       if(mwt.ne.0) then
03691         do i=1,ndata
03692           t=(x(i)-sxoss)/sig(i)
03693           st2=st2+t*t
03694           b=b+t*y(i)/sig(i)
03695         enddo
03696       else
03697         do i=1,ndata
03698           t=x(i)-sxoss
03699           st2=st2+t*t
03700           b=b+t*y(i)
03701         enddo 
03702       endif
03703       b=b/st2
03704       a=(sy-sx*b)/ss
03705       siga=sqrt((1.+sx*sx/(ss*st2))/ss)
03706       sigb=sqrt(1./st2)
03707       chi2=0.
03708       if(mwt.eq.0) then
03709         do i=1,ndata
03710           chi2=chi2+(y(i)-a-b*x(i))**2
03711         enddo 
03712         q=1.
03713         sigdat=sqrt(chi2/(ndata-2) )
03714         siga=siga*sigdat
03715         sigb=sigb*sigdat
03716       else
03717         do  i=1,ndata
03718           chi2=chi2+((y(i)-a-b*x(i))/sig(i))**2
03719         enddo 
03720         q=gammq(0.5*(ndata-2),0.5*chi2)
03721       endif
